  "body": "@dillonsvincent Suggested the following would be useful in the `truffle-dev` gitter:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nmodule.exports = (deployer, network, accounts, context) => {\r\n   if (context.command === 'test') \r\n     // do something...\r\n```\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\n{\r\n  command: <string>\r\n  options: <object>   // The command line options ?\r\n  reporter: <object>  // A reporter class that formats the migrations output (this is coming V5)\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis would address #847 and help make Migrations optional for tests without relying on shell environment variables.",
